        "evidence": "<p>Volume of Hemorrhage = A &times; B &times; C &times; Slices / Hemorrhage Shape</p>\n<p>A = Length<br>B = Width<br>C = Slice Width<br># Slices with Hemorrhage Present</p>\n<p><b>Hemorrhage Shape: If Round/Ellipsoid: 2; Otherwise: 3.</b> (See references below for this update to the formula.)</p>\n<p>Of note, the volume of an ellipsoid is 4/3 &times; &pi; &times; (ABC/2); when you estimate &pi; to be ~3, the volume becomes ABC/2.</p>",
